DriftSlide — Change Log
=======================

0.1.0 (unreleased)
-------------------
Initial release.

* OBS source plugin ("DriftSlide") registering as OBS_SOURCE_TYPE_INPUT.
* 4-state display cycle: Transparent → Fade In → Displaying → Fade Out.
* Configurable durations: transparent gap (1–3600 s), display (1–300 s),
  transition (0.1–10 s).
* Five transition styles: Fade, Slide Left, Slide Right, Slide Up, Slide Down.
* Directory scan with case-insensitive extension matching for PNG, JPEG, BMP,
  TGA, WebP, and GIF files.
* Alphabetic and random (Fisher-Yates shuffle) image ordering.
* Thread-safe settings handoff from UI thread to render thread via a
  pending-values / dirty-flag pattern.
* Premultiplied SRGB image loading and correct blend mode
  (GS_BLEND_ONE / GS_BLEND_INVSRCALPHA).
* Smooth easing via smoothstep on all transitions.
* Zero pixel output during the transparent interval — no black frames composited
  into the scene.
* UTF-8 path encoding when passing file paths to OBS image loader (fixes image
  discovery on Windows for directories with non-ASCII characters).
* Scan result logged to the OBS log at INFO level to aid debugging.
